<div class="comment-text">
<p>Oh dear.</p>
<p>Right off the bat we are told:</p>
<p>“The organization’s name derives from Abraham Lincoln’s Second Inaugural address, delivered while our country was on the precipice of a civil war, where he implored Americans to prevent difference from “break[ing] our bonds of affection,” and to appeal to “the better angels of our nature.”</p>
<p>And how did that turn out?</p>
