</ul><!-- end .comment-meta -->
</div><!-- end .comment-details -->
<div class="comment-text">
<p>We have the perfect solution built into our system of government already, it’s called Federalism!<br/>
We just need to put it back into use the way it was before the federal government became uber centralized after the civil war.<br/>
Take away as much power from the executive branch as possible, leave only foreign policy and the minimal amount of bureaucracy needed for interstate issues. Put the power back in the legislative branch and the states.<br/>
We have 50 states that are almost like their own countries (aka California, Texas for instance) let people run their own experiments in the states.</p>
